title: "[float_field()]{.doc-object-name .doc-function .doc-label .doc-label-function}"
body-classes: doc-api-page
page-navigation: false
html-table-processing: none
---

::: {.doc-subject}

Create a floating-point column specification for use in a schema.
:::

::: {.doc-usage-source}
Usage

[Source](https://github.com/posit-dev/pointblank/blob/main/pointblank/field.py#L530-L674){target="_blank" rel="noopener"}
:::

::: {.doc-signature .doc-Kind.FUNCTION}
```python
float_field(
    min_val=None,
    max_val=None,
    allowed=None,
    precision=None,
    nullable=False,
    null_probability=0.0,
    unique=False,
    generator=None,
    dtype="Float64"
)
```
:::

::: {.doc-text}

The `float_field()` function defines the constraints and behavior for a floating-point column
when generating synthetic data with `generate_dataset()`. You can control the range of values
with `min_val=` and `max_val=`, restrict values to a specific set with `allowed=`, enforce
uniqueness with `unique=True`, and introduce null values with `nullable=True` and
`null_probability=`. The `dtype=` parameter lets you choose between `"Float32"` and
`"Float64"` precision.

When both `min_val=` and `max_val=` are provided, values are drawn from a uniform
distribution across that range. If neither is specified, values are drawn uniformly from a
large default range. If `allowed=` is provided, values are sampled from that specific list.
:::

## Parameters {.doc-parameters}

::: {.doc-definition-items}
<code>[min_val]{.doc-parameter-name}[:]{.doc-parameter-annotation-sep} [float | None]{.doc-parameter-annotation} [=]{.doc-parameter-default-sep .op} [None]{.doc-parameter-default}</code>

:   Minimum value (inclusive). Default is `None` (no minimum).

<code>[max_val]{.doc-parameter-name}[:]{.doc-parameter-annotation-sep} [float | None]{.doc-parameter-annotation} [=]{.doc-parameter-default-sep .op} [None]{.doc-parameter-default}</code>

:   Maximum value (inclusive). Default is `None` (no maximum).

<code>[allowed]{.doc-parameter-name}[:]{.doc-parameter-annotation-sep} [list[float] | None]{.doc-parameter-annotation} [=]{.doc-parameter-default-sep .op} [None]{.doc-parameter-default}</code>

:   List of allowed values (categorical constraint). When provided, values are sampled from
    this list. Cannot be combined with `min_val=`/`max_val=`.

<code>[precision]{.doc-parameter-name}[:]{.doc-parameter-annotation-sep} [int | None]{.doc-parameter-annotation} [=]{.doc-parameter-default-sep .op} [None]{.doc-parameter-default}</code>

:   Number of decimal places to round generated values to. Default is `None` (no rounding).
    Must be a non-negative integer. Has no effect when `allowed=` or `generator=` is used.

<code>[nullable]{.doc-parameter-name}[:]{.doc-parameter-annotation-sep} [bool]{.doc-parameter-annotation} [=]{.doc-parameter-default-sep .op} [[False]{.va}]{.doc-parameter-default}</code>

:   Whether the column can contain null values. Default is `False`.

<code>[null_probability]{.doc-parameter-name}[:]{.doc-parameter-annotation-sep} [float]{.doc-parameter-annotation} [=]{.doc-parameter-default-sep .op} [[0.0]{.fl}]{.doc-parameter-default}</code>

:   Probability of generating a null value for each row when `nullable=True`. Must be
    between `0.0` and `1.0`. Default is `0.0`.

<code>[unique]{.doc-parameter-name}[:]{.doc-parameter-annotation-sep} [bool]{.doc-parameter-annotation} [=]{.doc-parameter-default-sep .op} [[False]{.va}]{.doc-parameter-default}</code>

:   Whether all values must be unique. Default is `False`. When `True`, the generator will
    retry until it produces `n` distinct values.

<code>[generator]{.doc-parameter-name}[:]{.doc-parameter-annotation-sep} [Callable[[], Any] | None]{.doc-parameter-annotation} [=]{.doc-parameter-default-sep .op} [None]{.doc-parameter-default}</code>

:   Custom callable that generates values. When provided, this overrides all other
    constraints. The callable should take no arguments and return a single float value.

<code>[dtype]{.doc-parameter-name}[:]{.doc-parameter-annotation-sep} [str]{.doc-parameter-annotation} [=]{.doc-parameter-default-sep .op} [[&quot;Float64&quot;]{.st}]{.doc-parameter-default}</code>

:   Float dtype. Default is `"Float64"`. Options: `"Float32"`, `"Float64"`.
:::

## Returns {.doc-returns}

::: {.doc-definition-items}
<code> [FloatField]{.doc-parameter-annotation}</code>

:   A float field specification that can be passed to `Schema()`.
:::

## Raises {.doc-raises}

::: {.doc-definition-items}
<code> [ValueError]{.doc-parameter-annotation}</code>

:   If `min_val` is greater than `max_val`, if `allowed` is an empty list, if
    `null_probability` is not between `0.0` and `1.0`, if `precision` is negative,
    or if `dtype` is not a valid float type.
:::

## Examples {.doc-examples}

The `min_val=` and `max_val=` parameters define the generated value ranges:

::: {#c90389f2 .cell execution_count=1}
``` {.python .cell-code}
import pointblank as pb

schema = pb.Schema(
    price=pb.float_field(min_val=0.01, max_val=9999.99),
    probability=pb.float_field(min_val=0.0, max_val=1.0),
    temperature=pb.float_field(min_val=-40.0, max_val=50.0),
)

pb.preview(pb.generate_dataset(schema, n=100, seed=23))
```

